		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/15/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 02:34:54</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=638"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=638')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=1491&FORUM_ID=6&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&Topic_Title=Verant%27s+caster+%22sacred+cows%22"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> If Verant is really serious about FINALLY balancing casters they are going to have to examine some of the caster "sacred cows". What I mean by this is that they have to realize that certain things need fundamental change.</P><P>We have just found out that staring at the spellbook now is GONE! All a player has to do now is to sit and meditiate. Nice to see that sacred cow finally bite the dust now that Brad is gone. This would have been unthinkable a year ago but it happened!</P><P>Here's what needs to change at level 60+<BR>----------------------------------------</P><P> -casters should no longer need to "sit" and medidate, standing will regen the same amount of mana (by level 60 it stands to reason a caster should have the skill to medidate sitting or standing)</P><P> -casters no longer should have to stand still and cast in order to avoid being "interrupted" (tanks can fight while moving, why can't casters cast while moving? spell refresh rates are penalty enough)</P><P> -pure casters should have 16 spell slots (there is no reason why a lvl 1 wizard(Harry Potter) should be able to memorize the same number of spells as a lvl 60 wizard (Gandalf the Grey).<BR> <BR> -healer casters (clerics, druids and shaman) should have 12 spell slots at lvl 60</P><P> -hybrids should have 10 spell slots at lvl 60</P><P> -pets should not steal experience regardless of how much damage they do (hybrid exp penalty anyone?)</P><P> -pets should be indifferent to all mobs in the same way that NPC pets con indifferent to players (Verant owes us this for the bad pathing they refuse to fix...my spec pet killed my whole group in Chardok when I sent him in to attack mobs just a few feet away from me, instead he travelled halfway across the zone and brought Hell back with him)</P><P>It's time to start thinking "out of the box" folks. We've all lived with these silly limitations in the name of BALANCE. Verant needs to show casters that they are SERIOUS for a change and make some sweeping changes. I know they read this board. Please Scott Hartsman and anyone from Verant consider some of these "sacred cows".</P><P>Thank you!</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer (retired)<BR>The Nameless</font></td>

      </tr>

