        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Can you imagine how powerful Druid/Wizzy quad-kiting would become if you could med standing AND cast while moving? </P><P>All of these are great suggestions with wonderful RP value - if it were just applied to necros. But with all the other classes in considering some of these would become incredibly unbalancing (quadding as one example). </P><P>Pet exp penalty is a crock-o-sheit. Fix it or bring back hybrid penalties. I feel sorry for SKs. They were getting the exp shaft up every hole they had.</P><P>As for WIS casters getting the same amount of spell slots as INT casters...  I think Clerics and Shamans should. Instead of being a focus for magical damage they are a pure focus for aiding others magically. </P><P>Druids are a different matter entirely. To me Clerics are clerics and Shamans are the clerics for the... erm... less advanced societies. I think its rather unfair to the Shamans (and no I do not nor have ever played a shammy or druid.. this is just my opinion from 3 years of playing this damn game) to continuously group their healing power with druids. They should be slightly better at it than the tree huggers. If I was doing the balancing I would need to look at druids seperately like bards since they dont really fit in to one of the 3 class types.</P><P>But then if I did the balancing wizzies could blow up freeport necros could solo inny clerics could do an AE manaless CH and I personally would have statues all over norrath which everyone had to pay homage to twice a day. *shrug* imperfect world  whatcha gonna do..</P><P>Aerich the Unguilded<BR>Warlock on CT<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
