        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=10604&TOPIC_ID=1491&FORUM_ID=6&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&Topic_Title=Verant%27s+caster+%22sacred+cows%22&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I'll agree with most of these ideas - to a degree.  As others have stated, 16 slots is a bit much.  Hell, I'd run out of spells befor I filled them up.  Plus, where on the screen would you put them?  Can't see the dragon past the spell gems.  </P><P>The standing while meditating is a decent idea - though the others are correct when they say that the quading power of wizards and driuds (which I absolutly despise anyway)would allow them to steal eveyone elses mobs twice as much as they already do.  Meditatin while running seems more likely to bump you in to a tree than be successfull.  </P><P>Casting while running is against the whole RP aspect (which Verant often takes in to consideratoin befor anything else).  Sure melee's can atack while moving, the intelligence required to jab a blade is minimal.  However, the mentaly taxing task of casting a firebolt or inducing a plague is significantly more attention-diverting.  Plus, kiting would be so insanely easy.</P><P>Regardless of how everyone treats it, I don't see how KSing your pet (or him KSing you) is all that big a deal.  Perhaps you all need to stop obsessing so much about the experience.  If my pet serves as an adequate body guard, he's more than welcome to the exp.  Now what would be awesome is - if the pet gains enough experience he should have stat/health bonuses.  Like leveling, I suppose, but with not so much exp required, and the stat/hp increase minimal.  While all the time we spend on raids, and in places like sebilis or velks alone, we could end up with a pet that is quite formidable.  There would be - of course - a cap to the levels allowed to pets.</P><P>In an RP aspect, a pet not pissing off people doesn't fit.  If I don't like you, and i see your pet running about, it's only smart that I'd follow the pet to reach you.  The bad pathing sucks, but note that programming is harder than many people think.  Program your own MMORPG befor you want to complain.</P><P>I have a feeling that no matter what chnges in EQ, poeple will never be pleased.  I guess it's in our nature.  But realize that you can't make everyone hunky-dory.  The only issue I'm begging for is DoT stacking.  That would fix SO much with necros and raid problems *sighs dreamily*</P><P>Daemian Sah'Thyr of Peep Cartouche<BR>Heretic of Druzzil Ro<BR>"The grass is always dead on my side of the fence"<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121263" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121263</a></P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
