        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> One of my ideas to have casters be able to stand while medding is because we get insane agro and hate from the mob when we are sitting. Tanks NEVER sit as you may have noticed so they are not forced to deal with this sitting = agro problem. Also tanks are given the AC, HPS and gear to take a beating, casters do not get any of this.</P><P>When I'm medding as a necromancer in raids in Lich form, I'm like a magnet for mobs, they can do 500 damage on me in a few seconds then they knock me right down again. This is something that needs to be seriously fixed. Let's see if Verant has the will.</P><P>There's another sacred cow that really bugs me. It's when I'm sitting the mob can hit me like I have zero AC. Just try sitting next to an orc pawn sometime and notice that he can hit you for full damage. That is just crazy...a lvl 1 orc doing damage to a lvl 60 caster?!?</P><P>Another problem is how NPC casters can land spells on lvl 60 players. The other day I was powerleveling a friend at the orc camp in West Commons. A level 5 Orc Apprentice blinded me. How is it possible for an NPC 55 levels lesser than me to be hit by a NPC caster?</P><P>Finally, I do not think it's unreasonable to ask for 16 spell slots at level 60. I don't think anyone can argue successfully that Harry Potter(lvl 1 wizard) should be able to mem the same number of spells as Gandalf the Grey(lvl 60 wizard) or Saruman the White. Yet we continue to believe this lie and work with a paltry 8 spell slots. I mean it's completely ridiculous that I have hundreds of spells yet as a master of my class I can only memorize 8 spells.</P><P>We are "casters" after all. Shamans, druids and clerics (healers) *should* get less because they have the a lot more AC than wizards, mages, chanters and necros and they are not pure casters. It's time for someone to ask these questions and get some answers from Verant. Casters need fundamental change to keep up with tanks, rogues and monks. Once upon a time EverQuest was balanced. Then Kunark came out and the Devs at Verant starting giving uber gear to melee classes. I'm just glad they finally woke up. I hope they are serious.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer (retired)<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
